# Pipeline Configuration — [Product Name]

> Maps this pipeline instance to target repositories for [Product Name].
> To activate: `cp pipelines/[product-name].md pipeline.md`

---

## Target Repositories

(REQUIRED — where does the code live?)

| Repository | Path | Purpose |
|-----------|------|---------|
| Primary | `/path/to/your/repo` | [e.g., Rails web app, Node.js API] |

> Each repository listed here should have a `PIPELINE.md` at its root with repo-specific config
> (branch conventions, framework, directory structure, test commands, guardrails, and any optional
> sections like API conventions or multi-tenant security).
>
> The primary repository's `PIPELINE.md` is the one skills read most — it has the framework details,
> directory structure, and implementation order that drive Stages 1-7.
>
> ### Required PIPELINE.md fields used by skills
>
> **Repository Details:**
> - Default branch, Conventions file, Test command, Test directory, Branch prefix, PR base branch
> - **App type** — `web-api`, `web-only`, `api-only`, `cli`, `desktop`, or `library`
> - **Platform label** — Human-readable name for commit messages and reports (e.g., `Rails`, `Phoenix`, `Django`)
>
> **Framework & Stack:**
> - Language, Framework, Test framework, ORM, Database, etc.
> - **Syntax check** — Command to verify file syntax (e.g., `ruby -c {file}`, `elixir -c {file}`, `node --check {file}`)
> - **Debug patterns** — Regex of debug artifacts to check for (e.g., `binding\.pry\|puts\|pp\|debugger\|byebug`)
> - **Seed command format** — How to run seed/data tasks (e.g., `bundle exec rake {task}`, `mix run {task}`)
> - **Test data pattern** — How test data is set up: `factories`, `fixtures`, or `manual`

